<h1>Supplier Portal & SQA Management System</h1>
<p style="font-size: 12pt; color: #64748b; font-style: italic;">Technical Architecture & System Overview</p>

<p>This document outlines the software architecture, data structures, and functional components built for the Supplier Portal & SQA Management System to present to Sakthi Auto Component's IT and management teams.</p>

<h2>1. Core Technology Stack</h2>
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th style="width: 25%;">Technology Layer</th>
      <th style="width: 30%;">Software / Library</th>
      <th style="width: 45%;">Purpose & Function</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td><b>Application Framework</b></td>
      <td>Next.js 16 (React 19)</td>
      <td>Handles both the frontend user interface rendering (Server-Side and Client-Side rendering) and backend REST API handlers in a unified, modern web workspace.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><b>Database</b></td>
      <td>MongoDB & Mongoose ODM</td>
      <td>Cloud-native, document-oriented NoSQL database used to store accounts, logs, audits, and settings with high scaling performance.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><b>Styling / UI Elements</b></td>
      <td>Tailwind CSS & shadcn/ui</td>
      <td>Responsive utility-first styling framework combined with interactive accessible UI modules to ensure the portal fits mobile and desktop viewports.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><b>Data Visualization</b></td>
      <td>Recharts</td>
      <td>Renders live charts and performance dashboards for daily production, dispatch, rejection, and inventory risk trends.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><b>Email Notification System</b></td>
      <td>EmailJS / SMTP Server</td>
      <td>Automatically sends critical notifications (e.g. stock shortages, report uploads) to supplier, SQA admin, and purchase departments.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><b>Deployment & Caching</b></td>
      <td>Vercel</td>
      <td>Edge-optimized cloud hosting server providing continuous deployment, serverless runtime, and static assets caching.</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h2>2. Cloud Database Collection Schemas</h2>
<p>The system features four primary database schemas modeled using Mongoose:</p>

<h3>A. Users & Supplier Profiles (User Collection)</h3>
<p>Stores supplier profiles containing approved components, tax IDs, and safety stock levels.</p>
<ul class="bullet-list">
  <li><b>approvedParts</b>: Defines the components the supplier is certified to supply, specifying <i>partNumber</i>, <i>name</i>, and <i>debitAllowance</i> (allowed rejection % tolerance).</li>
</ul>

<h3>B. Performance Log (Production Collection)</h3>
<p>Tracks daily material balance logs submitted by suppliers and verified by the SQA team.</p>
<div class="formula">
  Closing Stock = Opening Stock + Casting Issued + Production - Rejection - Dispatch
</div>
<ul class="bullet-list">
  <li><b>enteredBy</b>: Distinguishes whether the log was entered by the <i>Supplier</i> or created/modified by the <i>Admin</i> for complete auditability.</li>
</ul>

<h3>C. Live Production Lines (SettingChange Collection)</h3>
<p>Tracks the active component running on each of the supplier's pre-machining lines (maximum of 5 lines).</p>

<h3>D. Rejection Debit Notes (DebitNote Collection)</h3>
<p>Manages rejection charges exceeding allowance thresholds.</p>
<div class="formula">
  Allowance Qty = Received Qty * (Allowance % / 100)<br>
  Exceed Qty = Max(0, Rejection Qty - Allowance Qty)<br>
  Total Debit Amount = Exceed Qty * Recovery Rate
</div>

<h2>3. Key System Features</h2>
<ul class="bullet-list">
  <li><b>Dual Portal RBAC</b>: Separates SQA Admin features (complaints tracking, debit notes, audit uploads) from Supplier tools (daily logging, line change overrides, report downloads).</li>
  <li><b>Automated Alerts</b>: Dispatches email notifications when daily logs show a closing balance under 100 units (Red Alert) or under 500 units (Orange Alert).</li>
</ul>

</body>
